This paper deals with a communication protocol for IoT devices, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of multipacket reception and retransmission strategies, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of packet collision resolution, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for improved throughput, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
